LAGOS â€“ Jumia Nigeria said its customers would enjoy exciting deals from top-tech brands as the Jumia Tech Week started on Monday. The Jumia Tech Week, the company said would run until April 3, 2022. A statement by the media consultant to the company said that during the two-week-long campaign, Jumia would be providing consumers with the opportunity to get the best deals on the latest tech devices such as mobile phones and accessories, TVs, computers, cameras, video games and much more. The statement hinted that Jumia is giving consumers a wide selection of products to shop through its partnership with global tech brands such as Samsung, HP, Umidigi, Fitbit, Oraimo, Edifier, Anker and Xiaomi. Speaking on the campaign, Massimiliano Spalazzi, Jumia Nigeria Chief Executive Officer (CEO), said the Jumia Tech Week allows consumers to buy tech-related items at the best prices. He said that for the 2022 edition, the company has extended the campaign to two weeks to give its consumers more time to shop for their tech devices. According to him, the campaign caters for everyone with tech-related needs: working-class professionals and students in need of laptops and storage devices; gamers in need of the latest game console and video games; gadget lovers wanting to upgrade to the latest phones and entertainment lovers in need of speakers and television sets to create a home cinema experience.